        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 9 at 11:56AM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 1156 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Whitehead, or near Sparta, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Galax...
Hillsville...
Sparta...
Independence...
Fries...
Mc Grady...
and Laurel Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
